==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rive
<hw>Rive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos>
<conjf>Rived</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. p.</pos> <conjf>Rived</conjf>
or <conjf>Riven</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Riving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Icel. <ets>r⟦imac⟧fa</ets>, akin
to Sw. <ets>rifva</ets> to pull asunder, burst, tear, Dan.
<ets>rive</ets> to rake, pluck, tear. Cf. <er>Reef</er> of land,
<er>Rifle</er> a gun, <er>Rift</er>, <er>Rivel</er>.]</ety> <def>To rend
asunder by force; to split; to cleave; <as>as, to <ex>rive</ex> timber
for rails or shingles</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall <qex>ryve</qex> him through the sides twain.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The scolding winds have <qex>rived</qex> the knotty oaks.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brutus hath <qex>rived</qex> my heart.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rive
<hw>Rive</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be split or rent
asunder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Freestone <qex>rives</qex>, splits, and breaks in any
direction.</q> <rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Rive
<hw>Rive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A place torn; a rent; a rift.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rivel</ent>⟦br⟧
